title: Coronavirus Highlights: Maharashtra reports 66,836 new Covid-19 cases
description: Coronavirus Highlights April 23: India on Friday reported 3,32,730 fresh Covid-19 new cases in the last 24 hours, the highest single-day tally any country reported ever since the pandemic began last year. Meanwhile, 2,263 more people succumbed to the infection, taking the nationwide toll to 1,86,920, according to the data provided by the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare on Friday morning. With fresh Covid-19 cases, the country's active caseload stands at 24,28,616, while total recoveries has increased to 1,36,48,159. Amid this massive surge in Covid-19 cases across India, Prime Minister Narendra Modi will hold a series of meetings on Friday over the coronavirus situation in the country. With rising cases, the second wave of the pandemic has raised new fears about the crumbling health services as several states struggle with a shortage of oxygen and ICU beds. Follow Indiatoday.in for LIVE updates on the coronavirus situation in India and across the world.
